19/09/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Commercial flights between Belgrade and New York were reinstated Thursday (18 September) after an 11-year break. 
Serbian Minister of Transport and Telecommunications Marija Raseta-Vukosavljevic and US Ambassador William Montgomery attended a ceremony marking the occasion. 
Both sides agreed the resumption of flights is a major step forward in enhancing relations.Serbian Trade and Tourism Minister Slobodan Milosavljevic and world-famous basketball players Vlade Divac and Marko Jaric were on the first plane. 
(B92, Tanjug, BBC, FoNet - 18/09/03)
